      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PIPALICIOUS (7) kept her manners in check last start and went close, coming from the back row to miss by a head when second at Bendigo. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position and she'll need to be on her best behaviour but can win with her A-game. Manners have let THE TROUT COD (1) down in both starts so far but she started favourite last time so suspect there is ability there. Gets the ace draw and the penny could drop. HEIR JAURDON (6) showed improvement to place at start number two. Draws wider but has scope for further progression. WAR DAN PHOENIX (3) drops in grade on the last attempt and led from wider than this for a resuming placing prior.",
